   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate Innovation Advocacy and Lobby</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Addressing climate contentious issues in our work will enable us to drive climate policy in regions to create enabling environments for climate adaptation and mitigation impact globally. In 2019, we f developed the climate risk/vulnerability analysis and the Climate Smart Index (CSI), both tools to measure climate -risk responsiveness and adaptation measurement, as well as GHG calculators to measure GHG mitigation impact. We developed commodity-specific definitions and climate-risk responsive measures for coffee, cotton, palm oil, and  tea. 

The CSI was tested with 52,012 farmers in 4 different projects (sugarcane Brazil, sugarcane India, Coffee East Africa and Palm Oil Nicaragua). It is an important tool to assess the impact and effectiveness of climate smart (adaptation) practices at farm level.</narrative>
  </description>
